 "description": "Vessel speeds by oar (slow/cruise/fast on fatigue: fresh crews 30 factors, Vikings 40; rest regains 1, slow spends 2, cruise 3, fast 10) and by sail (paired figures: light-moderate / fresh-strong breeze). Speed changes are stepwise (fast→slow→stop→back...); current adds or costs 5\"; backing is half; rivers halve sailing. Wind: 2d6 — 2-3 calm (oars only), 4-8 light-moderate, 9-11 fresh-strong (galleys ship water 10%/turn, −25% speed each time, sinking at −75%), 12 gale (run before it at 3\"; galleys may founder). Wind direction d8 by compass point. Turning: 45° per 10\" rowed, 30° per 12\" sailed. Galleys shun open ocean; longships alone among the oar-pierced keep the seas.",
